claim.claim-text:
1. A system, comprising:
a memory to store instructions; and
a processor coupled to the memory, wherein responsive to executing the instructions, the processor performs operations comprising:
receiving a telephone number from a first communication device;
identifying a second contact book of a second communication device according to the telephone number;
submitting a notice to the second communication device describing a request from the first communication device to synchronize a first contact book with the second contact book of the second communication device;
submitting an authentication request to the first communication device for a verification code;
receiving one of the verification code corresponding to a personal identification number from the first communication device or an acknowledgment from the second communication device to provide authorization for the first communication device to synchronize the second contact book with the first contact book;
providing the first communication device with access to update in whole or in part the second contact book of the second communication device stored in a contact book account according to the authorization;
receiving from the first communication device an entry of the first contact book according to the access to update provided;
merging the entry of the first contact book with an entry of the second contact book to generate an updated second contact book;
storing the updated second contact book in the contact book account; and
synchronizing at the second communication device the updated second contact book with a second local contact book stored in the second communication device.

15. A non-transitory computer-readable storage medium, comprising instructions which, responsive to being executed by a processor, cause the processor to perform operations comprising:
receiving a telephone number from a first communication device;
identifying a second contact book of a second communication device according to the telephone number;
receiving from the first communication device a request to synchronize a portion of a first contact book of the first communication device with the second contact book of the second communication device;
submitting to the second communication device a notice of the request;
receiving an authorization indicator from one of the first communication device or the second communication devices, wherein the authorization indicator corresponds to a personal identification number;
synchronizing the portion of the first contact book with the second contact book responsive to a validation of the authorization indicator;
storing the first contact book that is synchronized in a contact book account of the second communication device; and
synchronizing at the first communication device the first contact book with a first local contact book stored in the first communication device.

19. A first communication device, comprising:
a memory to store instructions; and
a processor coupled to the memory, wherein responsive to executing the instructions the processor performs operations comprising:
transmitting to a system a telephone number of the first communication device, wherein a second contact book of a second communication device is identified according to the telephone number to synchronize a first contact book of the first communication device with the second contact book;
transmitting to the system a request to synchronize the first contact book of the first communication device with the second contact book of the second communication device;
receiving from the system a request for a verification code, wherein the verification code corresponds to a personal identification number;
transmitting to the system the verification code;
transmitting to the system the first contact book for synchronization with the second contact book responsive to the system indicating that the verification code is valid or responsive to the system indicating that the system has received authorization from the second communication device to initiate the synchronization; and
synchronizing the first contact book with a first local contact book stored in the first communication device.
